## Activity Log
- Session started. First session as Alpha. Goal: score > 10 in CogsVsClips.
- Plan: Review existing policy, run a test game, analyze results, iterate.
- Ran setup, installed cogames and mettagrid.
- Found mettagrid_sdk unavailable (not on PyPI). Existing semantic_cog.py depends on it.
- Created alpha_policy.py from scratch using only mettagrid base APIs.
- Discovered game mechanics through experimentation:
  - Move costs 4 energy. Solar gives 1 energy/tick.
  - Hub territory (strength 20, decay 1) heals +100 hp and +100 energy per tick.
  - Agents MUST stay within ~18 tiles of hub or they drain HP and die.
  - Hub starts with 24 of each element and 5 hearts.
  - Hearts cost 7 of each element from hub.
- v1 scored 0.18 (5 junctions aligned). Agents alive, mining, depositing.
- Key issues: some agents die leaving territory, not enough resource variety mined.
- v2: Added HP safety, range limiting, dead-reckoning navigation. No more deaths.
- v3: Fixed gear station offset coordinates (were x,y not row,col). Added systematic exploration.
- Discovered gear stations are outside initial 13x13 obs window - agents must navigate blind.
- Uploaded v15 and v16 to tournament. Best local score: 0.97 (avg ~0.1).
- Key remaining issues: agents with aligner+heart can't reliably find junctions to align.
- Tournament v14 scores 0.7-2.0. My policy underperforms - need mettagrid_sdk for existing policy.
- Ported mettagrid_sdk from metta-ai/metta repo (git clone with GITHUB_TOKEN).
- MettagridSemanticPolicy now loads and runs! Score 2.0-3.35 locally (203 alignments best).
- Uploaded as alpha.0:v17 with SDK bundled.
- Session ended. Merged all work to main.
